# Actual-Diff and Local Verification

Treat reports of intent as unverified until the repository proves the result.

- Inspect `git status` and the actual `git diff` before reporting implementation complete.
- Read and spot-check the files claimed to have changed.
- Run the smallest relevant deterministic local tests, build, lint, or validation commands.
- Confirm the checks exercise the requested golden path and material edge cases.
- If the diff is absent or differs from the report, state the discrepancy and do not claim completion.
- Report commands and outcomes accurately; do not turn skipped or unavailable checks into passes.
